 Business Briefs
																								 New Delhi, Nov. 8: Lakshmi Mittal is planning to buy a 50 per cent stake in Prize Petroleum, Hindustan Petroleum Corps exploration arm, for about Rs 200 crore. Mittal is in talks with financial institutions for the stake buy, sources said. The steel baron is looking for a medium-sized firm involved in exploration and production. He has looked at a few firms but nothing is finalised just now, sources added.																								 Calcutta, Nov. 8: Balmer Lawrie has earmarked Rs 300 crore for organic and inorganic growth, according to a strategic plan prepared by the firm for 2012. Managing director S.K. Mukerjee said the company was looking for inorganic growth in construction chemicals, leather chemicals, tourism and logistics.																								 Mumbai, Nov. 8: BM Khaitan group firm McLeod Russel will seek shareholders approval for its proposed investment of Rs 50 crore in D1 Williamson Magor Bio Fuel. The company will purchase equity shares in the company and or give a loan of up to Rs 50 crore.																								 New Delhi, Nov. 8: Ranbaxy has reached an agreement with Astellas Boehringer Ingelheim in a patent case over Flomax (R) (Tamsulosin capsules) used in the treatment of benign enlargement of prostate. Ranbaxy will now be able enter the us market on March 2, 2010.
